# Number Recognition Project

This project implements and compares **multiple machine learning and deep learning models** for handwritten digit recognition using the **MNIST dataset**.  
The goal is to evaluate the performance of different architectures and visualize their predictions, accuracy, and losses.

---

## üìù Models Implemented

### 1. CNN (Basic Convolutional Neural Network)
- **Architecture:** 3 convolutional layers, max pooling, dropout, fully connected layers.
- **Accuracy:** ~98%
- **Strengths:** Simple, fast, baseline CNN.

**Visuals:**

<div style="margin-top: 50px;">
    ![CNN Training Curve](result/cnn_model/images/training_curve.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![CNN Sample Prediction](result/cnn_model/images/sample_prediction.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![CNN Confusion Matrix](result/evaluation/CNN_confusion_matrix.png)
</div>

---

### 2. MLP (Multilayer Perceptron / Fully Connected Network)
- **Architecture:** 4 fully connected layers with dropout and ReLU activation.
- **Accuracy:** ~97%
- **Strengths:** Simple fully connected network, no convolutional layers.

**Visuals:**

<div style="margin-top: 50px;">
    ![MLP Sample Prediction](result/evaluation/MLP_sample_0.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![MLP Confusion Matrix](result/evaluation/MLP_confusion_matrix.png)
</div>

---

### 3. Advanced CNN
- **Architecture:** 4 convolutional layers, batch normalization, dropout, max pooling, 3 fully connected layers.
- **Accuracy:** ~99%
- **Strengths:** Deeper network, better regularization, highest performance among CNN models.

**Visuals:**

<div style="margin-top: 50px;">
    ![Advanced CNN Training Curve](result/advanced_cnn/images/training_curve.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![Advanced CNN Sample Prediction](result/advanced_cnn/images/sample_prediction.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![Advanced CNN Confusion Matrix](result/evaluation/Advanced_CNN_confusion_matrix.png)
</div>

---

### 4. ResNet18 (Transfer Learning)
- **Architecture:** Pretrained ResNet18 (ImageNet) with final layer modified for 10 classes. Input resized to 224√ó224.
- **Accuracy:** ~99%
- **Strengths:** Uses transfer learning, robust feature extraction, high performance on small datasets.

**Visuals:**

<div style="margin-top: 50px;">
    ![ResNet18 Sample Prediction](result/resnet/images/sample_prediction.png)
</div>

<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
    ![ResNet18 Confusion Matrix](result/evaluation/ResNet18_confusion_matrix.png)
</div>

