## ‚ö° Key Differences Between Models

| Model          | Type              | Accuracy | Complexity | Key Feature                           |
|----------------|-----------------|----------|------------|---------------------------------------|
| MLP            | Fully Connected  | 97%      | Low        | Simple, no convolution                |
| CNN            | Convolutional    | 98%      | Medium     | Baseline CNN                          |
| Advanced CNN   | Convolutional    | 99%      | High       | BatchNorm, Dropout, deeper layers    |
| ResNet18       | Transfer Learning | 99%     | High       | Pretrained features, robust          |

- **MLP:** Quick to train, limited feature extraction.  
- **CNN:** Learns spatial features, good for image recognition.  
- **Advanced CNN:** Handles overfitting better, deeper features, highest accuracy.  
- **ResNet18:** Leverages transfer learning, robust and fast convergence.

---

## üìÇ How to Run

1. Train any model:

```bash
python Train_Code/cnn_model.py
python Train_Code/mlp_model.py
python Train_Code/advanced_cnn_model.py
python Train_Code/resnet_mnist.py
Evaluate all models:

bash
Copy code
python evaluate_all_models_visual.py
All results, metrics, plots, and sample predictions will be saved in the respective result/ folders.

